Adora Fertility is one of Australia's leading fertility providers and closely
aligns with what we are and who we aspire to be; a team of compassionate and
specialised healthcare professionals, utilising modern science to improve the
chances of conception for our patients.

We fundamentally changed the fertility landscape by making high quality
fertility services including IVF available with almost all costs covered by
Medicare, saving patients thousands of dollars compared to other fertility
clinics.

** About the Role **

We are looking for our next ** Fertility Coordinator! ** This is a full-time
opportunity based in our Taringa Clinic.

As first point of contact for our patients, we are seeking that special
individual with genuine warmth, attentiveness, and positivity. The primary
purpose of this role is to provide a high-quality service and support to the
healthcare professionals, nurses and patients in our Fertility unit.

** Key Responsibilities **

  * Preparing patient packs for upcoming nursing consults 
  * Preparing patient packs for repeat cycles and mailing them 
  * Creating and filling patient checklists as part of preparation for cycles. 
  * Emailing/Mailing pathology forms and scan referrals to patients when required. 
  * Ensuring all checklists complete in our Patient Management System and that all consent forms and screening bloods are current as patients are commencing a treatment cycle. 
  * Manage patient collection trays and pending consent documents. 
  * Ensure all collateral patient material is topped up and order through marketing as required. 
  * Ensuring medical records, including results, correspondence and any other related material are up to date and filed correctly and in a timely fashion. 
  * Manage outbound calls for general patient enquiries via email/website. 
  * Manage patient enquiries as deemed appropriate for skillset as triaged by Nursing team and admin. 

** About you **

To be considered for this role, you will possess the following:

  * Minimum 2 years’ experience in a Customer Service or Administration role preferably in a healthcare environment 
  * Excellent interpersonal and communication skills 
  * A patient-centred warm and caring approach 
  * Excellent verbal and written communication skills 
  * Strong computer skills 
  * Willingness to learn and grow with the business 
  * Full training will be provided 

** Benefits **

  * Join a safe & inclusive workplace that emphasises its employee's wellbeing and development. 
  * Access to our Employee Assistance Program and free counselling sessions. 
  * Discounts on our Adora Fertility Services. 
  * Paid Parental Leave Allowance - 10 weeks. 
  * Local Social Activities 

At Adora, we believe in living our values every day. We are committed to
Social Responsibility, Integrity, Empathy, Teamwork, Respect and Excellence.
If you share those values and want to contribute to a likeminded team, we
invite you to join us, please select the ‘APPLY’ button to submit your
application.

